[30;1m229 | [0m[35mIf the default declarative NLA map is not flexible enough, one[0m
[30;1m230 | [0m[35mcan use a custom map adapter. In order to do so, one should define[0m
[30;1m231 | [0m[35mat least one function to return `pyroute2.netlink.NlaSpec()`, and[0m
[30;1m232 | [0m[35mone optional function to tell the parser if the attribute is supported.[0m
[30;1m233 | [0m[35mThe simplest definition only to decode packets:[0m
[30;1m234 | [0m[35m[0m

[30;1m48 | [0m[35mPyroute2 runs natively on Linux and emulates some limited subset[0m
[30;1m49 | [0m[35mof RTNL netlink API on BSD systems on top of PF_ROUTE notifications[0m
[30;1m50 | [0m[35mand standard system tools.[0m

[30;1m52 | [0m[35mOther platforms are not supported.[0m

[30;1m76 | [0m[35m    # of the remaining time until T2 (in RENEWING state) and one-half of[0m
